"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-anne-hidalgo-paris-olympics-2024-river-seine-swim-b1171177.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  News|World  Paris MayorAnne Hidalgohas fulfilled a promise to swim in the Seine in a bid to show it is clean ahead of the SummerOlympics.  The swim took place on Wednesday morning along a stretch of the river that passes by Paris' City Hall and the Notre Dame Cathedral.  Ms Hidalgo was joined by Tony Estanguet, head of the Paris 2024 Games, and Marc Guillaume, the prefect of the Paris region.  The official made a pledge in January to swim in the river to highlight its improved cleanliness. French Sports Minister Am\\u00e9lie Oud\\u00e9a-Cast\\u00e9ra, also swam in the Seine on Saturday wearing a full-body suit.  Ms Hidalgo had initially planned to swim in the Seine in June,but it was delayed due to the calling of snap Parliamentary elections.  On the initial date, the hashtag \\\"jechiedanslaSeine\\\" or \\\"I am pooping in the Seine\\\" trended on social media as some threatened to protest the Olympics by defecating upstream.  The Summer Games will kick off on July 26 with a lavish open-air ceremony that includes an athletes' parade on boats on the Seine.  Since 2015, organisers have invested millions of pounds to prepare the Seine for the Olympics and to ensure Parisians have a cleaner river in the years after the Games.  The plan included constructing a giant underground water storage basin in central Paris, renovating sewer infrastructure, and upgrading wastewater treatment plants.  However, concerns over the Seine's flow andpollutionlevels have persisted, prompting daily water quality tests by the monitoring group Eau de Paris.  Results in early June indicated unsafe levels of E. coli bacteria, but this appears to have improved.  Venezuelan Nobel Peace Prize winner gives her medal to Donald Trump  The London Standard best photos from around the world  Astronauts land in SpaceX shuttle after evacuation from International Space Station  Is coffee the future of socialising? This stylish spot thinks so  Despite being a recurring promise among politicians, swimming in the Seine has been banned\\u00a0for over a century.  Jacques Chirac, the former French president, made a similar pledge in 1988 when he was Paris mayor, but it never came to pass.  The Seine will host several open water swimming events during the Games, including marathon swimming at the Olympic Games and the swimming legs of the Olympic and Paralympic triathlons.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"